title: Mary Cassatt The Child’s Bath Unmatted Print
description:
Print developed from Mary Cassatt’s The Child’s Bath, 1893, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

In The Child’s Bath (1993), Mary Cassatt addressed the theme for which she is best known—women and children—while also experimenting with compositional elements of Japanese art. The Child’s Bath is the culmination of her investigation of a flattened picture plane and decorative patterning.

  • Print Reproduction
  • Image size: 15 x 9.75 in.
  • Poster size: 12 x 16 in.
  • Materials: Premium Cardstock
